LAGOS – Following their victory over African counterpart, Sudan, today at the ongoing African Cup of Nations, AFCON, in Cameroon, PDP chieftain, Alhaji Atiku Abubakar has hailed the Super Eagles of Nigeria for their doggedness on the field of play. According to him, the Super Eagle’s win today was a “Textbook Victory” worthy of celebration, as well as a worthy gift to the nation’s fallen heroes, in remembrance of their gallantry and bravery in their line of duty. “Textbook victory over Sudan. Well done, Super Eagles, @NGSuperEagles. An excellent result to celebrate as a country, and also a gift to the remembrance of our gallant armed forces. #AFCON2021#NGASUD“, he wrote on his official twitter handle, @atiku. Presidential Aspirants Fail To Excite Electorate Olubadan: Controversies Resolved, Ladoja Affirms Lekan Balogun See tweet below;